## Parent Epic: Span Highlighting (git_safety_guard-jpfm)

## Objective

For consistency, the dcg test command should also show highlighted matches when a command would be blocked. This helps users understand pattern behavior without triggering hook mode.

## Current dcg test Output

Command: [command]
Result: BLOCKED
Pack: [pack]
Pattern: [pattern]
Reason: [reason]

## Enhanced Output

Command: git reset --hard HEAD
         ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
         └── Matched span

Result: BLOCKED
Pack: core.git
Pattern: reset-hard
Reason: Destroys uncommitted changes

## Implementation Steps

1. Locate test command handling in src/cli.rs
2. Reuse highlight formatter from src/highlight.rs
3. Add span display after command line
4. Ensure consistent formatting with hook output

## Consistency Goal

Both hook mode denials and dcg test should use the same highlighting logic, ensuring users see identical output regardless of how they invoke DCG.

## Acceptance Criteria

- dcg test shows highlighted span for blocked commands
- Format matches hook denial output
- Reuses shared highlight formatter
- Works for allowed commands too (no highlight needed)

## Dependencies

- Task: Create terminal formatter (must be complete)

