 {"id":"git_safety_guard-h272","title":"[E10-T6] Integration with severity levels","description":"## Task: Integration with severity levels

### Parent Epic
Epic 10: Graduated Response System (git_safety_guard-yejh)

### What To Do
Ensure graduated response respects pattern severity levels.

### Implementation Details
1. Severity-based graduation override:
   ```rust
   fn get_graduation_mode(
       severity: Severity,
       config: &ResponseConfig,
   ) -> GraduationMode {
       // Check severity-specific override
       if let Some(mode) = config.severity_overrides.get(&severity) {
           return mode.clone();
       }

       // Default: critical always hard blocks
       if severity == Severity::Critical && config.mode != GraduationMode::Disabled {
           return GraduationMode::Paranoid;
       }

       config.mode.clone()
   }
   ```

2. Graduation decision:
   ```rust
   fn determine_response(
       command: &str,
       pattern: &Pattern,
       session_count: u32,
       history_count: u32,
       config: &ResponseConfig,
   ) -> GraduatedResponse {
       let mode = get_graduation_mode(pattern.severity, config);

       match mode {
           GraduationMode::Paranoid => GraduatedResponse::HardBlock { ... },
           GraduationMode::WarningOnly => GraduatedResponse::Warning { ... },
           _ => {
               // Apply graduation logic based on counts
               if history_count >= config.history_hard_block {
                   GraduatedResponse::HardBlock { ... }
               } else if session_count >= config.session_soft_block {
                   GraduatedResponse::SoftBlock { ... }
               } else {
                   GraduatedResponse::Warning { ... }
               }
           }
       }
   }
   ```

3. Special handling:
   - Critical severity: always hard block (configurable)
   - Low severity: warn only (configurable)
   - Medium/High: use graduation

