### Parent Epic
Epic 6: Temporary/Expiring Allowlist Entries (git_safety_guard-2fma)

### What To Do
Implement allowlist entries that expire when the shell session ends.

### Session Tracking Options

OPTION 1: Environment Variable
- Set DCG_SESSION_ID on first invocation
- Check if still same session on subsequent calls
- Pros: Simple, works across shell commands
- Cons: Can be spoofed, survives shell restart if exported

OPTION 2: Parent Shell PID
- Store parent shell PID with rule
- Check if parent still alive
- Pros: Accurate session detection
- Cons: PID reuse (rare), cross-platform differences

OPTION 3: TTY/PTY Identifier
- Store TTY device with rule
- Check if still same TTY
- Pros: Good session proxy
- Cons: May not work in all environments

RECOMMENDED: Hybrid approach
- Generate session ID from: PID + TTY + start time
- Store in temp file: /tmp/dcg-session-{hash}
- Check file existence and content

### Implementation
```rust
fn get_session_id() -> String {
    let ppid = std::process::parent_id();
    let tty = get_tty().unwrap_or_default();
    format!("{}-{}", ppid, tty)
}

fn is_same_session(stored_id: &str) -> bool {
    get_session_id() == stored_id
}
```

